    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with a lineup anchored by two high-ceiling plays: **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (80.98) and **Trea Turner** (70.16). **Pete Crow-Armstrong** is our premier play, benefiting from a soft matchup against Sasaki (5.52 xERA) and favorable wind conditions. His dynamic platoon advantage against the right-handed starter boosts his floor, making him an essential start despite hitting in the bottom third of the order. Meanwhile, **Trea Turner** remains the engine of our offensive production; his matchup against Elder (4.29 xERA) combined with an optimal leadoff spot provides a strong foundation for both run production and our priority category of stolen bases. **Junior Caminero** (71.50) and **Kyle Schwarber** (66.62) round out our top-tier starters, both benefiting from favorable SP skill metrics that elevate their daily output.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the morning involved **Victor Scott II** (38.48), who narrowly missed the starting lineup. While his elite speed makes him a frequent target for our roster goals, his matchup against Woo (3.30 xERA) significantly depressed his ceiling, pushing his efficiency score below our 40-point threshold for active play. We have opted to prioritize the higher-upside profiles of **Chase Meidroth** and **Caleb Durbin** in the utility and infield slots, despite their pedestrian positions in the order, to avoid the risk of a \"Below Floor\" performance. Elsewhere, we are monitoring the status of **Christian Yelich** and **Gary Sanchez**, both unavailable due to injury or rest, while **Carson Benge** is locked out by a rainout. As we look to maintain our momentum, we are keeping a close eye on **Hyeseong Kim**; though he has a promising score of 57.38 driven by wind-assisted power and platoon edges, he remains susceptible to the defensive efficiency of the opposing team, and his position at #8 in the lineup limits his overall run-scoring potential compared to the top-of-the-order anchors like **Yordan Alvarez** and **Colt Keith**.",
